<div style="text-align:justify">

''Shadow'' was well-received by the media, with an average critic score of 91% at [[Game Rankings]],<ref name="gamerankings">{{cite web | title=Gamerankings: Shadow of the Colossus | url=http://www.gamerankings.com/htmlpages2/924364.asp | accessdate=December 22 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> making it the 14th-highest rated game of 2005. These include the Japanese magazine ''[[Famitsu]]'', who rated the game 37/40,<ref name="famitsuscore">{{cite web | author=Freund, Josh | year=2005 | title=News – Latest Famitsu scores – Shadow of the Colossus, Battalion Wars, more | url=http://www.gamesarefun.com/news.php?newsid=5685 | work=[http://www.gamesarefun.com/ GamesAreFun.com] | accessdate=August 3 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> the [[United Kingdom|UK]]-based ''[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]]'', who awarded an 8/10,<ref name="edge">{{Cite book | year=2005 | editor=Editors of Edge magazine | title=Edge Christmas 2005; issue 157 | pages=98–99 | language=English | publisher=Future Publishing}}</ref> and ''Electronic Gaming Monthly'', who granted 8.8/10.<ref name="egmsoty" /> [[GameSpot]]'s review gave it an 8.7, commenting that "the game's aesthetic presentation is unparalleled, by any standard",<ref name="gamespotreview" /> while multimedia website [[IGN]] hailed the game as "an amazing experience" and "an absolute must-have title", rating it 9.7/10.<ref name="ignreview2">{{cite web | author=Roper, Chris | year=2005 | title=Shadow of the Colossus Review | url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/658/658991p3.html | work=[http://ign.com/ IGN] | accessdate=July 21|accessyear=2006}}</ref> [[GameSpy]] described it as "possibly the most innovative and visually arresting game of the year for the PS2".<ref name="gamespyreview">{{cite web | author=McGarvey, Sterling | year=2005 | title=Shadow of the Colossus Review | url=http://ps2.gamespy.com/playstation-2/ico-ii/658966p1.html | work=[http://gamespy.com/ GameSpy] | accessdate=July 21 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> A retrospective ''Edge'' article described the game as "a fiction of unquestionable thematic richness, of riveting emotional power, whose fundamental artistic qualities are completely fused with its interactivity."<ref name="edge100">{{Cite book | year=2007 | editor=| title=Edge Presents The 100 Best Videogames| pages=pp. 146 | language=English | publisher=Future Publishing}}</ref>

Many reviewers consider the game's soundtrack to be one of its greatest aspects. In addition to ''Electronic Gaming Monthly''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s award of "Soundtrack of the Year",<ref name="egmsoty" /><ref name="scores">{{cite web | editor=GameSpot site staff | year=2005 | title=Shadow of the Colossus for PlayStation 2 Reviews | url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/adventure/wandaandthecolossus/review.html?mode=web | work=[http://www.gamespot.com/ GameSpot] | accessdate=July 30 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> GameSpot commented that the musical score conveyed, and often intensified, the mood of any given situation,<ref name="gamespotreview" /> while it was described as "one of the finest game soundtracks ever" by a reviewer from [[Eurogamer]].<ref name="eurogamer" />

However, the game has been negatively criticised for its erratic [[frame rate]], which is usually smooth while traversing the landscape, but often slows down in fast-paced situations, such as colossus battles.<ref name="gamespotreview" /> Concern was also expressed about the game's camera, which was described by GameSpy as being "as much of an opponent as the Colossi", "manag[ing] to re-center itself at the worst and most inopportune times".<ref name="gamespyreview" /> Reviewers are often mixed about Agro's AI and controls, while gaming website Thunderbolt insists the realism of his movement and behaviour "create[s] a videogame experience unlike any other"<ref name="thunderbolt">{{cite web | author=Kramer, Josh | year=2005 | title=Shadow of the Colossus Review | url=http://www.thunderboltgames.com/reviews/viewreview.php?rid=767 | work=[http://www.thunderboltgames.com/ Thunderbolt] | accessdate=July 25 | accessyear=2006}}</ref>. ''Edge'' comments that the controls are "clumsy, crude, and unpredictable".<ref name="edge" /> Other critics like [[Game Revolution]]<ref name="gamespyreview">{{cite web | author=Ben Silvermen | year=2005 | title=Shadow of the Colossus Review | url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/oldsite/games/ps2/adventure/shadow_of_the_colossus.htm | work=[http://www.gamerevolution.com/ Game Revolution] | accessdate=January 3 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> and Gamespot felt the game was too short-lived (average playthrough time estimated 6 to 8 hours), with little replay value.

===Awards===
''Shadow of the Colossus'' has received several awards, including recognition for "Best Character Design", "Best Game Design", "Best Visual Arts" and "Game of the Year", as well as one of three "Innovation Awards" at the 2006 Game Developers Choice Awards.<ref name="eurogamer3">{{cite web | author=Fahey, Rob | year=2006 | title=Colossus looms over GDC Awards | url=http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=63539 | work=[http://www.eurogamer.net/ Euro Gamer] | accessdate=July 29 | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="gdc">{{cite web | author=Thorsen, Tor | year=2006 | title=Colossus casts shadow over GDC Awards | url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/adventure/wandaandthecolossus/news.html?sid=6146480 | work=[http://www.gamespot.com/ GameSpot] | accessdate=July 30 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> At the 2006 [[Digital Illusions CE|DICE]] Summit, the game won the award for "Outstanding Achievement in Art Direction" at the [[Academy of Interactive Arts & Sciences]],<ref name="aoiaas">{{cite web | author=GameSpy site staff | year=2006 | title=The 9th Annual Academy of Interactive Arts and Sciences Awards | url=http://www.gamespy.com/articles/687/687827p2.html | work=[http://www.gamespy.com/ GameSpy] | accessdate=July 30 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> while it received one of two "Special Rookie Awards" at the Famitsu Awards 2005.<ref name="famitsuawards">{{cite web | author=Famitsu.com site staff | year=2006 | title="FAMITSU AWARDS 2005"大賞は『キングダム ハーツII』と『バイオハザード4』!! | url=http://www.famitsu.com/game/news/2006/04/21/103,1145605197,52094,0,0.html | work=[http://www.famitsu.com/ Famitsu.com] | accessdate=August 3 | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="famitsuawards2">{{cite web | author=Sony Computer Entertainment staff | year=2006 | title=Shadow of the Colossus 日本サイト | url=http://www.jp.playstation.com/scej/title/wander/prize.html | work=[http://www.shadowofthecolossus.com Shadow of the Colossus official site] | accessdate=August 3 | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="famitsuawards3">{{cite web | author=Gantayat, Anoop | year=2006 | title=New Awards Discovered in Famitsu Awards Presentation | url=http://games.ign.com/articles/702/702910p1.html | work=[http://ign.com/ IGN] | accessdate=August 3 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> It was nominated for "Best Original Music", "Best Artistic Graphics" and "Best PS2 Game", yet also "Most Aggravating Frame Rate" in GameSpot's awards for 2005,<ref name="awardnom">{{cite web | author=GameSpot site staff | year=2005 | title=GameSpot's Best of 2005 – Special Achievement Awards | url=http://gamespot.com/pages/features/bestof2005/index.php?day=2&page=1 | work=[http://gamespot.com/ GameSpot] | accessdate=July 18 | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="awardnom2">{{cite web | author=GameSpot site staff | year=2005 | title=GameSpot's Best of 2005 – Special Achievement Awards | url=http://gamespot.com/pages/features/bestof2005/index.php?day=2&page=8 | work=[http://gamespot.com/ GameSpot] | accessdate=18 July | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="awardnom3">{{cite web | author=GameSpot site staff | year=2005 | title=GameSpot's Best of 2005 – Special Achievement Awards | url=http://gamespot.com/pages/features/bestof2005/index.php?day=2&page=5 | work=[http://gamespot.com/ GameSpot] | accessdate=July 18 | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="awardnom4">{{cite web | author=GameSpot site staff | year=2005 | title=GameSpot's Best of 2005 – Special Achievement Awards | url=http://gamespot.com/pages/features/bestof2005/index.php?day=2&page=4 | work=[http://gamespot.com/ GameSpot] | accessdate=July 18 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> while it won "Best Adventure Game" and "Best Artistic Design" in IGN's  Best of 2005 awards,<ref name="ignawards">{{cite web | editor=IGN site staff | year=2005 | title=IGN.com presents The Best of 2005 | url=http://bestof.ign.com/2005/overall/2.html | work=[http://ign.com/ IGN] | accessdate=July 19 | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="ignawards2">{{cite web | editor=IGN site staff | year=2005 | title=IGN.com presents The Best of 2005 | url=http://bestof.ign.com/2005/overall/14.html | work=[http://ign.com/ IGN] | accessdate=July 19 | accessyear=2006}}</ref><ref name="ignawards3">{{cite web | editor=IGN site staff | year=2005 | title=IGN.com presents The Best of 2005 | url=http://bestof.ign.com/2005/overall/25.html | work=[http://ign.com/ IGN] | accessdate=July 19 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> who cited Agro as the best sidekick in the history of video games<ref name="agrotop10">{{cite web | author=IGN site staff | year=2006 | title=Top 10 Tuesday: Best Sidekicks | url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/698/698916p1.html | work=[http://ign.com/ IGN] | accessdate=July 29 | accessyear=2006}}</ref>. Two years after its release IGN listed ''Shadow'' as the fourth greatest PlayStation 2 game of all time.<ref name="ign25best">{{cite web| author=Dunham et al | year=2007 | title=The Top 25 PS2 Games of All Time | url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/772/772296p1.html | work=[http://ign.com/ IGN] | accessdate=March 23|accessyear=2007}}</ref>Games Radar awarded it Best Game Of The Year 2006 (being released in the UK in early 2006, later than the US).<ref name="gamesradar">{{cite web | author=Games Radar Staff | year=2006 | title=Games Radar's 20 Best Games of 2006 | url=http://www.gamesradar.com/gb/xbox/game/features/article.jsp?articleId=20061222121859937003&releaseId=2006031312435546032&sectionId=1003&pageId=20061222122153390013 | work=[http://www.gamesradar.com/ Games Radar] | accessdate=December 22 | accessyear=2006}}</ref> The game's ending was selected as the fourth greatest moment in gaming by the editors of ''[[GamePro]]'' in July 2006.<ref name="gamepro">{{cite web | author=GamePro editors | year=2006 | title=The 55 Greatest Moments in Gaming | url=http://www.gamepro.com/gamepro/domestic/games/features/75048.shtml | work=[http://www.gamepro.com/ GamePro] | accessdate=July 31 | accessyear=2006}}</ref>



